AWS Support plans :
====================
	AWS Basic Support
		-	Customer Service & Communities - 24x7 access to customer service, documentation, whitepapers, and support forums. 
		-	AWS Trusted Advisor - Access to the core Trusted Advisor checks and guidance to provision your resources following best practices to increase performance and improve security. 

	
	Developer :
		-	Recommended if you are experimenting or testing in AWS.
		-	General Architectural Guidance
		-	only core checks from the AWS Trusted Advisor Best Practice Checks
		-	Allows one primary contact to open unlimited cases
		
	Business :
		-	Minimum recommended tier if you have production workloads in AWS
		-	Architectural Guidance Contextual to your use-cases
		-	24x7 phone based technical support for its AWS account.
		
	Enterprise On-Ramp:
		-	Recommended if you have production and/or business critical workloads in AWS.
		-	Architectural Guidance Consultative review and guidance based on your applications (one-per-year)
	
	
	Enterprise:
		-	Recommended if you have business and/or mission critical workloads in AWS.
		-	Achitectural guidance Consultative review and guidance based on your applications
		-	plan provides access to a designated Technical Account Manager (TAM)
		
	AWS Abuse team :
	
		-	Contact AWS abuse team for the following types of abusive behaviour
			-	Spam, port scanning, DDOS, copyright content distributing malware, Intrusions attempts
	
AWS Organizations :
===================
	-	AWS Organizations helps you to centrally manage billing; control access, compliance, and security; and share resources across your AWS accounts.
	-	You can remove an account from your organization only if the account has the information that is required for it to operate as a standalone account. 
	-	AWS Support does not need to help you in removing an AWS account from AWS Organizations.
	-	AWS Organizations is available to all AWS customers at no additional charge.
		
